1. Install development python and pip on your machine
	a. Debian: sudo apt-get install python-dev python-pip
	b. Fedora/RHEL: sudo yum install python-devel python-pip
2. Install the python virtual environment service
	a. pip install virtualenv
3. Create a new virtual environment in THIS directory
	a. virtualenv venv
4. Activate the environment
	a. source venv/bin/activate
5. Install the dependencies
	a. pip install -r requirements.txt
6. Run the server
	a. python daytrip/serve.py
7. Deactivate your environment when finished
	a. deactivate